incidents.commentary: OUT! BOWLED! ALL OVER FOR PAKISTAN! New Zealand win it by 60 runs! Matt Henry bowls it fuller, from over the wicket, and around middle and leg, Naseem Shah moves across again and misjudges the line and length as he looks to scoop it over short fine leg but misses and falls over as the ball goes and rattles the leg stump.
On a good length, wide outside off, with pace off, Naseem Shah moves across and looks to squeeze it but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT! GONE THIS TIME! Pakistan are nine down! Mitchell Santner picks up his third wicket. He again gives air to the ball, around just outside off, Haris Rauf comes down the track and looks to loft it but loses his shape and completely mistimes it. The ball goes in the air towards long on where Michael Bracewell takes it with both hands. New Zealand are just one wicket away from the first win of the tournament.
SIX! ADD ONE MORE TO IT! Floated up, around off and middle, Haris Rauf uses his feet to get to the pitch of the ball and lofts it over long on for a biggie.
Drags his length, around off, Naseem Shah dabs it wide of point for a single.

SIX! Naseem joins the party now. Floated up, around middle, Naseem Shah goes on his knee and slogs it against the turn over deep mid-wicket for a biggie. 250 UP FOR PAKISTAN, something to cheer for the spectators.

Tossed up, around off, Naseem clears out his front leg and looks to loft it inside out over cover but gets it through the outer half of the bat as the ball just clears the backward point fielder and they run for a couple.
Nagging length, just outside off, Naseem makes room and looks to cut it but misses.
Change of pace, slower full ball, around leg, Haris stays low and looks to slog it but misses.
SIX! Rauf is enjoying his batting. Back of a length, around middle, from over the wicket, Haris Rauf stays on the back foot and drags it to deep backward square leg with a pull shot for a biggie.
On a good length, around middle and leg, follows the batter again, Naseem makes room and pushes it to long on for a single.
Back of a length, around leg, follows the batter, Rauf gets cramped up for room but manages to drop it down towards square leg for a single.
BEATEN! Short of a length, and outside off, Haris Rauf has a swing at it but misses.
Good length, around leg, coming in with the angle, Naseem Shah looks to flick it but misses and wears it on the pad. They run a single for a leg bye as the ball rolls away towards square leg.

SIX! WOW! JUST OVER BUT WHAT A SHOT FROM HARIS! Mitchell Santner tosses up, around middle and leg, Haris Rauf walks down the surface and slogs it down the ground just over leaping long on fielder for a biggie.
Slower through the air, ,around middle, Haris drops it down back to the bowler.
Nagging length, just outside off, Naseem steers it to deep cover for a single.
Keeps it shorter, around off, Naseem punches it but straight to cover.
Drags his length, just outside off, Naseem guides it to short third.
Tossed up, around off, Naseem Shah looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
A sharp bouncer, around middle, Haris Rauf ducks it.
On a good length, around middle and leg, Haris Rauf looks to guide it towards deep third but misses and wears it on the thigh pad.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is it from an entertaining knock from Khushdil Shah! Will O’Rourke gets his third wicket. What a bowler this bloke has been in the last few months. O'Rourke bowls on back of a length, from around the wicket, on middle. Khushdil Shah looks to pull it but gets cramped up for room and mistimes it towards long on where Michael Bracewell doesn't have to move an inch as he pouches it with a reverse cup. Shah departs after a fighting 69 off 49, and Pakistan are 229/8.
On a good length, around off, Shah mistimes it back to the bowler with the bottom part of the bat.

FOUR! A GEM OF AN INNING FROM KHUSHDIL! Back of a length, with pace off, around middle, trying to deceive the batter, Khushdil presses back and manages to pull it along the ground wide of deep fine leg for a boundary.
On a good length but wide outside off, keeps it away from the batter, Khushdil Shah extends his arms and looks to go over cover but only manages to toe end it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, around off, Khushdil Shah presses back and pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
A brilliant yorker from Henry, right in the blockhole, Khushdil Shah jams it out to the right of the bowler.
On a hard length, outside off, Naseem hops up a bit and guides it to deep third man for a single.
Henry again switches to around the wicket and bowls on a back of a length, around off, Khushdil opens the face of the bat and guides it to deep cover for a single.
FOUR! MUSCLED! Henry comes over the wicket and bowls on good length, around off, Khushdil Shah gives himself room as he clears out his front leg and thumps it over mid off for a boundary.
WIDE! Back of a length but wide outside off, Khushdil Shah looks to chase it with his stretched hands but misses. Called a wide.
FOUR! KHUSHDIL IS KEEPING PAKISTAN ALIVE! Slower length ball, from around the wicket, on middle, Khushdil Shah covers the line and pulls it along the ground towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a good length, around off, Shah dabs it towards cover point for a single.
WIDE! Short of a length, but wide outside off, Khushdil dances down the track and looks to chase it but misses. Called a wide.
FOUR MORE! THUMPED! Back of a length, around middle, Khushdil Shah stays on the back foot and pulls it along the ground towards deep mid-wicket for another boundary.

FOUR! In the air but a boundary! Short of a length, from around the wicket, on middle, Khushdil Shah presses back and pulls it. He gets cramped up for room and thus mistimes it. The ball goes in the air towards deep square leg where Devon Conway is a bit late in reacting and he even tries to slide forward to stop the ball or go for a catch. But the ball falls ahead of him and goes over the ropes for a boundary. Khushdil brings up his fifty also with this shot. Is there a glimmer of hope for Pakistan?
A tight single! Short of a length, around off and middle, Naseem dabs it wide of cover and runs off for a quick single.
WIDE! Bangs in short of a length, but down the leg side, Naseem Shah ducks and it is called a wide.
Could have been chopped on! Back of a length, around off, Naseem Shah waits for it and then opens the face of the bat but gets late and manages to get a thick inside edge onto the pads.
On a good length, outside off, Khushdil Shah walks down the track and looks to drag it to the leg side but gets a top edge that flies towards deep third and they run for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Pakistan are seven down! Matt Henry picks up his first wicket finally as he bowls on a back of a length, from over the wicket, outside off, Shaheen Afridi gets width so he extends his arms and looks to pull it but the ball skids through the surface and takes the outside edge and goes to the keeper Tom Latham who takes it to his right with both hands. Pakistan are 200/7.
On a good length, outside off, Khushdil Shah dabs it wide of backward point for a single. 200 comes up for Pakistan.

In the air but falls in the vacant region! On a good length, outside off, from over the wicket, Shaheen Afridi clears out his front leg and looks to slog it down the ground but mistimes it completely as the ball goes in the air but falls ahead of the long off fielder and they take a single.
Short of a length, around middle, Khushdil Shah transfers his weight to the back foot and looks to pull it but gets it through the top edge towards deep square leg for a single.
Comes around the wicket, on a good length and outside off, Khushdil Shah cuts it off the back foot but straight to point.
Back of a length, around middle, Shaheen Afridi stands tall and pulls it along the ground to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Short and around off, Shaheen Afridi backs away and punches it through covers for one.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Khushdil Shah sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Flatter, full and on leg, Khushdil Shah clips it towards square leg.
SIX! Clean strike! Tossed up, full and around off. Khushdil Shah moves across a bit and slogs it away powerfully over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
Short and outside off, Khushdil Shah cuts it to point.
Floated, full and on off, Shaheen Afridi pushes it through covers for a single.
Quicker, full and around off, Khushdil Shah reverse sweeps it straight to short third.
Floated, full and on middle, Khushdil Shah defends on the front foot.
Fires one full and on off, Khushdil Shah looks to reverse paddle it but misses.
Flighted, full and around off, turns away, Khushdil Shah goes down to sweep but misses.
Short and on middle, Khushdil Shah nudges it wide of deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs more.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Khushdil Shah tucks it towards deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Darts one full and n leg, Khushdil Shah clips it through mid-wicket for one.
Short and around off, Shaheen Afridi punches it past short covers for a single.
Flighted, full and on middle, Shaheen Afridi blocks it out.
Flatter, full and on middle, Shaheen Afridi guides it to point.
Floated, full and on middle, Shaheen Afridi steers it off the outer half of the bat to point.
SIX! BOOM! Tossed up, full and on middle. Shaheen Afridi skips down the track and dispatches it over the bowler's head with ease for a biggie.
FOUR! Flighted full and around off. Khushdil Shah goes down and drags his sweep nicely to the deep mid-wicket fence for another boundary.
Short and on off, Khushdil Shah punches it towards short covers.
Quicker, full and on off, Khushdil Shah goes down across to paddle but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Flatter, short and on middle, Khushdil Shah pats it down the pitch.
FOUR! Streaky! Tossed up, full and on middle, Khushdil Shah goes for the sweep but gets a top edge. It goes over square leg and spins away to the fence for a boundary.
Short and on leg, Shaheen Afridi clips it through square leg for a single.
FOUR! Nicely done! Flatter, full and on off. Khushdil Shah goes down and plays the reverse sweep to perfection wide of deep point for a boundary. They need a lot more of these.
Slows it up, full and on off, turns in, Khushdil Shah tucks it to the leg side.
Drags his length back, on off, Khushdil Shah pats it to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Shaheen Afridi goes for the big slog but gets an inside edge through square leg for a single.
Short again and outside off, Khushdil Shah cuts it to deep point for a run.
FOUR! Good shot! A half-tracker, on middle. Khushdil Shah rocks back quickly and smashes it away to the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Looped up, full and on middle, Khushdil Shah goes for the reverse sweep again but gets it from the toe-end onto his pad as the ball rolls to the off side. They cross.
Short again and on off, Khushdil Shah stabs it to short covers.
A bit short and on off, Shaheen Afridi pushes it towards covers for a run.
Flighted, full and on middle, Khushdil Shah reverse sweeps it to deep point for a single.
And again! Tossed up, full and on for, turns away sharply, Khushdil Shah prods forward to block but the ball turns past the outside edge.
BEAUTY! Floated, full and on off, turns away, Khushdil Shah stays back to play but gets beaten all ends up.

OUT! TAKEN! Mitchell Santner strikes again! He tosses it up nicely, full and on for, turns away a bit. Babar Azam goes down for the big sweep but only manages to get a top edge. The ball goes up in the air and Kane Williamson at mid-wicket takes a nice catch. Babar goes back for 64, and Pakistan are 153/6, still needing 168 runs in 96 balls.
Slows it up, full and on off, Babar Azam uses his feet and steers it towards backward point.
FOUR! Put away! Flighted, full and on middle. Babar Azam goes down and heaves it away to the deep mid-wicket fence for a bodunary. 150 up for Pakistan!
Short again and on leg, Khushdil Shah nudges it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Flatter, full and on leg, Babar Azam clips it wide of short mid-wicket for a quick run.
Floated, short and on middle, turns in, Khushdil Shah flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
A sharp bouncer, on middle, Khushdil Shah gets hurried into his pull shot and gets a top edge that lands safely in the square leg region. They cross.
On a length and on middle, Khushdil Shah tucks it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Nice shot! Nathan Smith bangs this one into the pitch and outside off. Khushdil Shah frees his arms and crunches it past point for a boundary.
Back of a length and around off, Khushdil Shah dabs it past point. The fielder from sweeper covers runs to his right and stops it with his foot. Two runs taken.
Short of a length and on off, Babar Azam runs it down to third man for a single.
SIX! Breaks the shackles a bit! Fuller one and on middle, angling in. Babar Azam picks it up nicely and whips it over the deep square leg fence for a biggie.
Short again and outside off, Babar Azam punches it to sweeper covers for one.
Flighted, full and on middle, Babar Azam tucks it to short mid-wicket.
Short and on middle, Khushdil Shah nudges it through mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! TAKEN! Mitchell Santner joins the party now! He drags his length back and on middle, quicker too. Tayyab Tahir tries to rock back and pull it away but gets a bit cramped up as the ball skids through. He loses his balance. He ends up hitting it flat and uppishly straight to short mid-wicket where Kane Williamson takes a sharp catch. Pakistan lose half their side now!
Floated, full and on middle, Tayyab Tahir blocks it out.
TURN AND BOUNCE! Tossed up, full and on off, grips and turns away with bounce. Tayyab Tahir looks to play but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Hard length and on off, Tayyab Tahir guides it through point for one more.
Short of a length and on off, Tayyab Tahir dabs it to point.

OUT! TAKEN! Nathan Smith strikes in his first over! The change of bowling has worked for the Kiwis. He bangs this one short and on middle. Salman Agha comes down the track to pull it away but the ball gets big on him. It takes the top edge and loops in the air. Michael Bracewell from short mid-wicket takes a couple of steps to his front and gobbles it up. Agha walks back after a quick-fire 42 off 28 balls. Pakistan are 127/4 now!
Back of a length and on off, Babar Azam steers it through backward point for another run.
On a length and on middle, Salman Agha backs away and pushes it towards covers for a run.
FIFTY FOR BABAR! A decent knock but he knows the job is not done yet! Fuller and on middle, Babar Azam clips it through square leg for a single.
Floats the ball up on the off stump. Salman Agha taps it late but finds the short third man fielder this time.

Floats the ball up wide outside off. Salman Agha goes for a sweep but misses. Tom Latham grabs the ball well and takes the bails off in a flash. The Third Umpire is consulted but Salman Agha looks comfortably in.
Just short outside off, turning away. Salman Agha nudges it to the left of short third man for a couple of runs this time. Moves onto 41 off just 24 deliveries now.
Nails a yorker on the stumps. Babar Azam drives it to long on for one.
Touch fuller on off. Babar Azam blocks it off the front foot.
Drops the ball short on top of the stumps. Babar Azam pulls it up and over mid-wicket for a quick couple.
Touch fuller on the off stump line. Babar Azam blocks it off the front foot.
Short and wide outside off. Salman Agha nudges it to the left of third man and a rare misfield from the fielder results in three runs by the batters.
FOUR! SECOND BOUNDARY OF THE OVER! Nagging length from Glenn Phillips and Salman Agha walks in and slogs the ball infront of deep square leg this time to pick up a boundary.
SIX! THAT IS HUGE! Salman Agha gets hold of that one. Tossed up from Glenn Phillips outside off and Salman Agha walks in and slogs the ball up and over long off for a huge six.
Just short on the stumps. Babar Azam flicks the ball to fine leg and runs a single.
Tossed up on the stumps. Babar Azam walks in and drops the ball down.
Full on the stumps. Babar flicks it to the right of Kane Williamson at short mid-wicket for a risky run.
Good length outside off Babar stays back, opens the bat face and guides it to backward point.
A flighted delivery around the off stump. Salman gets down on one knee and sweeps it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Full on the off stump. Salman reads it off the pitch and gets an inside edge to short fine leg.

FOUR! OUTSIDE EDGE! TWO IN TWO! Very full and outside the off stump. Salman gets low on the front foot for the sweep. It is too full to play the shot and he adjusts his stroke by opening the bat face and squeezing it past short third man to his left. The ball runs away to the fence in no time.
FOUR! SLAPPED AWAY! Around the wicket. Short and outside the off stump. Salman plays with the spin as he rocks back and slaps it past diving backward point to his left.
Touch fuller on off. Babar Azam blocks it off the front foot.
Nagging length spinning back into the stumps. Babar Azam blocks it off the front foot.
Full outside the off stump. Salman kneels down and sweeps it to the right of Conway at deep square leg for a run.

FOUR! CHEEKY! Full on the off stump. Slightly quicker from Phillips. Salman is down on one knee and uses the pace and spin of the bowler, scooping it over the keeper to his left for a cheeky boundary.

FOUR! UP AND OVER! Good pick shot by Salman Agha! Welcome boundary for Pakistan! They need more of these! Shortish length outside off. Spins back into Salman and stays low. The Pakistan number 5 rocks back and does well to get under it. Launches the ball up and obver covers for a superb boundary on the bounce.
Over the wicket. Short and outside off. Babar cuts it to deep cover for a single.
Nagging Good length around the off stump. Salman stays back and punches it to point.
Tossed up on the off stump. Salman is down on one knee and sweeps it off the inner half of the bat to short fine leg.
Another nagging length and outside off. Salman punches it to cover point.
Nagging length ball coming in with the arm on the middle and leg. Salman misses the whip on the inside edge and gets hit on the front pad. Slight appeal for lbw but it is going down leg.
Tossed up outside off. Babar Azam drives the ball to sweeper covers for a run.
Comes around the wicket and angles the ball on the off stump from a fuller length. Babar Azam taps it back to the bowler.
Nagging length outside off. Babar Azam walks in and drops the ball down towards covers.
Fuller on the stumps. Babar Azam drives the ball to long on for a single.
Fuller on the stumps. Salman Agha slogs the ball to deep mid-wicket for one.
On the pads from a nagging length. Babar Azam slaps it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Much fuller on off. Babar Azam drives the ball straight to mid off.
Drops the ball short outside off. Babar Azam taps it late, straight to Kane Williamson at short third man.
Short and wide outside off. Babar Azam slaps the ball to sweeper covers for a single.
Pitches it up on the stumps. Salman Agha sweeps the ball to deep square leg for one.
Nagging length on the off stump. Salman Agha blocks it off the front foot.

FOUR! VERY LUCKY! Mitchell Santner tosses the ball up on the leg stumps and gets a good turn away from the right-hander. Salman Agha looks to flick the ball but catches the leading edge that goes past the wicketkeeper for a lucky boundary.
Fast and flat on the stumps, moving away from the leg stumps. Salman Agha walks down and gets a hit on the thigh pads.
Tossed up on the stumps. Salman Agha walks in and slogs the ball into the mid-wicket gap for a couple of runs.
Drops it short on the stumps. Babar Azam tucks it towards square leg to end the over.
Touch fuller on off. Babar Azam flicks it to mid-wicket.
Nagging length on the stumps. Babar Azam turns it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller on off. Babar Azam blocks it off the front foot.

INSIDE EDGE! Tosses the ball up on the off stump line. Babar Azam dances down the track and goes for a wild slog. The ball hits the inside edge of the bat and runs away past the square leg. The batters pick up a couple.
Just short on the stumps. Babar Azam flicks the ball straight to square leg.
Fuller on the middle stump line. Salman Agha drives it back to the bowler.
Nagging length on the off stump. Babar Azam flicks the ball to long on for one.
Floats it up on off. Babar Azam drives it well but another brilliance from Glenn Phillips at covers and the batters are denied a single.
Tosses the ball up pon the off stump. Babar Azam drops it down towards point.
Touch fuller on the off stump. Babar Azam offers a front foot block.
Starts off short on the off stump. Babar Azam taps it straight to covers form the back foot.
Floats the ball up on the off stump. Salman Agha blocks it off the front foot.

OUT! TIMBER! Fakhar Zaman has to walk back after a disappointing outing! Michael Bracewell strikes for New Zealand! Michael Bracewell tosses the ball up on the off stump line. Fakhar Zaman takes away the front leg and looks to slog the ball. He misses it completely and the ball rushes onto hit the middle stump. Fakhar Zaman walks back for 24 (41) and Pakistan is 69/3 now.
Nagging length on the stumps. Babar Azam flicks the ball to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Touch fuller on the stumps. Babar Azam blocks it off the front foot.
Big turn from the stumps. Babar Azam gets some bat on it and the ball runs away to the fine leg area. The batters run a couple.
Floats the ball up outside off. Babar Azam takes a long foot outside off and wears the ball on the pads.
Floated up, around off, Fakhar Zaman looks to sweep it but gets it through the outer half of the bat towards short third man.
Nagging length, around off, Fakhar Zaman defends it.

DROPPED! It will be a bit harsh to call this a drop but at this level, and with New Zealand are so good with their fielding, it could have been caught. Glenn Phillips tosses up, around off, tempting the batter to go for a big shot, Fakhar Zaman goes on his knee and sweeps it but mistimes his shot completely. The ball takes the top edge and goes towards deep square leg. Devon Conway runs in forward and makes a full stretched dive to catch it with both hands but the ball bursts out through his hands. The batters don't run.
Quicker, around middle, Fakhar Zaman goes on the back foot and pushes it to cover.

Keeps it shorter, around middle, Babar Azam stays on the back foot and clips it wide of square leg and runs off for a quick single. Matt Henry collects the ball and makes a direct hit at the non-striker's end where Babar Azam is a bit lazy in running. New Zealand appeal but the umpire thinks that Babar has made it to the crease.
Nagging length, around middle, Babar Azam tucks it to square leg off the back foot.
Fuller, around middle, Fakhar Zaman comes forward and blocks it right under his eyes.
Nagging length, outside off, Fakhar presses back and drops it down to cover.
Tossed up, around middle, Zaman defends it.
Drags his length and keeps it wide of outside off, turns away further, Fakhar Zaman leaves it as it was way outside of his reach.
FOUR! STRONG STRIKE! Floated up, around middle, Fakhar Zaman goes on his knee and gets to the pitch of the ball to loft it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up, around middle, Babar turns it away to deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up, around middle, Babar Azam clips it towards square leg for a single.
Much slower through the air, around middle, Fakhar Zaman goes on his knee and looks to slog it but gets it through the bottom edge of the bat to deep square leg for a single.
Drops it much shorter and outside off, Fakhar Zaman makes room and eases out to backward point.
Floated up, around off, Babar comes down the track and pushes it to long on for a single.
Tossed up, around off, Fakhar Zaman uses his feet to get to the pitch of the ball and looks to loft it over mid-wicket but manages to toe-ends it to deep square leg for a single.
On a nagging length, around off, Babar Azam presses back and steers it to deep cover for a single.
A MAIDEN! Floated up, around off, Fakhar comes forward and drops it down to cover.
Tossed up, around off, Zaman doesn't offer any shot at it.
Keeps it much shorter, around off, Fakhar Zaman looks to turn it to the leg side but gets a leading edge back to the bowler.
Good bounce and turn! Nagging length, around middle, turns away with an extra bounce, Fakhar Zaman goes on his knee and looks to sweep it but misses.
Much slower, around off and middle, Zaman looks to drive it but toe-ends it back to the bowler.
Nagging length, on top of off, Fakhar Zaman lets the ball come to him and then opens the face of the bat to guide it to short third.
Tossed up, around off, Babar Azam lunges and looks to work it away to the leg side but gets a thick outside edge towards point.
Gives air to the ball again, fuller, around off, Fakhar Zaman comes down the track and pushes it to deep cover for a single.
Slower through the air, around middle, Fakhar looks to turn it to the leg side but misses and wears it on the pads.
Floated up, outside off, Babar comes forward and drives it wide of cover for a single.

FOUR! FLURRY OF BOUNDARIES! On a nagging length, around middle, Babar Azam presses back and swipes out towards wide of deep fine leg for a boundary. Matt Henry makes a dive to his left but can't save the boundary.
Tossed up, around off, Babar gets an inside edge towards square leg as he looks to defend it.

FOUR! CRUNCHED IT ABSOLUTELY! Floated up, around off, Fakhar Zaman again drags it towards deep square leg but more finely this time with a sweep shot for a boundary. There is no chance for the fielder this time.
Nagging length, around off, Zaman drops it down back to the bowler.

FOUR! GETS THE BOUDNARY NOW! Tossed up, around off, Fakhar Zaman goes on his knee and drags it towards deep backward square leg with a sweep shot. The ball races away to the boundary beating the diving deep square leg fielder.
A big turner! Similar length and outside off, turns away sharply, Fakhar Zaman goes on his knee and looks to sweep it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Nagging length, outside off, turns away, Fakhar Zaman defends it.
Too slower through the air, around off, fuller, Fakhar Zaman looks to drag it to the leg side with a sweep shot but toe-ends it back to the bowler.
Comes over the wicket, tossed up, around off, Babar Azam dabs it towards point and wants to have a single but is sent back by Fakhar Zaman.
Keeps it shorter, around off, Zaman taps it in front of point and runs off a quick single.
Drags his length a bit, and around off, slower through the air, Fakhar Zaman makes room and looks to slap it away but gets it through the inner half of the bat towards cover.
FOUR! PUNISHED! Again much slower and fuller, around off, Fakhar Zaman charges down the track and hammers it over the head of the bowler for a boundary.
Much slower, around off, Fakhar Zaman lunges and defends it.
Nagging length, around off, Babar Azam pushes it towards long on for a single.
Slower through the air, around off, Fakhar Zaman comes forward and blocks it out.
Fuller again, just outside off, Fakhar goes on his knee and looks to sweep it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Floated up, around off, Fakhar Zaman pushes it towards cover.
Tossed up, around off, Zaman drops it down to cover point.

Wonderful effort in the field again from New Zealand! Tossed up, around off, Fakhar Zaman goes on his knee and looks to sweep it. He mistimes it and the ball goes high in the air towards deep backward square leg. Nathan Smith runs into his left and saves the boundary with a dive and restricts the batter to just a couple of runs.
BEAUTY! From around the wicket, on the nagging length, turns away, around off, Fakhar Zaman goes on the back foot and looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a good length, outside off, Babar again cuts it hard but straight to that man again, Glenn Phillips at point. NO RUN.

FOUR! JUST SHORT OF THE FIELDER AND A BOUNDARY! Back of a length, outside off, Babar Azam extends his arms and crunches it aerially over extra cover. The ball goes in the air and just drops ahead of the diving deep cover fielder Devon Conway and goes over the ropes on the bounce for a boundary.
A good bouncer in a comeback from Will O’Rourke and Babar Azam ducks under it.
Hard length, outside off, Babar Azam gets enough room to free his arms as he slashes it hard but straight to the point fielder, Glenn Phillips.
FOUR! MAGNIFICENT TIMING! On a good length, on top of off, Babar Azam lets the ball come to him and then opens the face of the bat to just tap it in the gap finely towards deep third for a boundary.
On a hard length, around off, Zaman clips it wide of mid-wicket for a single.

Slower through the air, around off, Fakhar Zaman charges down the track and looks to heave it to the leg side but gets a leading edge as the ball goes high in the air and just over backtracking point fielder. They run for a single.

Drags his length a bit after seeing batter coming down the track, around middle, Fakhar Zaman gets cramped up for room and manages to just tap it towards cover and wants to have a quick single but is sent back by Babar Azam.
Tossed up, around off, from over the wicket, Fakhar Zaman goes back and defends it with the full face of the bat.
Floated up, around middle, Babar Azam uses his feet and pushes it to long on for a single.
Similar line and length, around middle, Babar comes forward and drops it down.
Tossed up, around off, Babar Azam defends it back to the bowler.

OUT! TAKEN SUPERBLY! Glenn Phillips, you beauty! Will O’Rourke bangs this one short and outside off, Mohammad Rizwan looks to cut it over point but does not quite get the elevation but hits it really hard. The ball travels fast and hard wide of point. Phillips flies to his left to pluck that one out of thin air with his outstretched left hand. He just keeps taking these spectacular catches. Pakistan lose their skipper and in a lot of trouble now.
Overpitched and on middle, Babar Azam drills it wide of mid off for a single.
Touch fuller and on off, Babar Azam drills it to short covers. Pakistan need to get a move on here.
On a length and on off, Babar Azam steers it to point.
Slower one, back of a length and around off, Babar Azam misses out on his cut shot.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam pushes it to short covers.
Overpitched and on off, Mohammad Rizwan keeps it out to the off side.

Hard length and on off, Babar Azam looks to play at it but gets a bottom edge on the ground and wide of the keeper. Tom Latham dives to his right and makes a half-stop wth his outstreched right hand. They cross.
Pulls his length back, on off, Babar Azam pushes it to short covers.
Pitched up and on middle, Babar Azam blocks it out.
Good length and on middle, nips back in sharply, Babar Azam looks to work it away but misses and gets hit on the pads. A loud appeal for LBW, but turned down.
Fuller and on middle, Mohammad Rizwan clips it through mid-wicket for a single.
JAFFA! Will O’Rourke hits the length had and around off, nips back in viciously. Babar Azam looks to play at it but gets squared up as the ball zips past his bat.
FOUR! Nice shot! Overpitched and outside off. Babar Azam gets the chance to free his arms and carves it through point for a boundary.
Pitched up and on off, Mohammad Rizwan drives it to covers for a single.

O'Rourke nails the yorker, on middle, angling in. Mohammad Rizwan is a bit late to put his bat down and gets hit on the pads. The ball goes towards backward point and Rizwan sets off for the run but is sent back in time.
Short of a length and outside off, Mohammad Rizwan cuts it hard but straight to point. The dots are piling up here.

Uppish but safe! Will O’Rourke bangs this into the pitch and on middle, shaping in. Mohammad Rizwan looks to pull but geta a bit hurried. It goes off the gloves into his shoulder and pops up but lands well wide of the keeper.
Touch fuller and on off, keeps a bit low, Babar Azam gets low and keeps it out to the off side. MAIDEN OVER!
Hard length and on off, Babar Azam stabs it towards cover-point.
Short of a length and around off, Babar Azam punches it to extra covers.
Good length and on middle, Babar Azam blocks it out well.
Overpitched and on off, Babar Azam drills it to mid off.
Full and on middle, Babar Azam knocks it towards mid on.
Bangs this into the pitch, outside off, Mohammad Rizwan leaves it alone.
back of a length and on off, Mohammad Rizwan stabs it towards short covers.
Short of a length and outside off, Mohammad Rizwan looks to cut but gets a bottom edge on the bounce to the keeper.
Hard length and on off, Babar Azam runs it down to third man for one.
Fuller and on middle, shaping in, Mohammad Rizwan flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Good length and around off, Mohammad Rizwan steers it towards point.
Pitches it up, on middle, shaping in sharply. Babar Azam steps across to work it away but misses and gets hit on the pads. A huge shout for LBW, but turned down. Probably going down the leg side.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Matt Henry goes a bit too full and on off. Babar Azam leans on to his drive nicely and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Back of a length and on middle, Babar Azam punches it to mid on. Four dots in a row now!
Pitched up and on middle, angling in, Babar Azam blocks it out solidly.
Good length and on off, Babar Azam looks to push it away but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam fends it to the off side.
Pitches it up around off, Mohammad Rizwan pushes it to short covers.
Fuller and on off, Mohammad Rizwan taps it to short covers.

OUT! TAKEN! Will O’Rourke draws first blood! He bowls this on a hard length and outside off. Saud Shakeel's eyes lit up seeing the width on offer and he slashed hard at it. However, he is not in control of the shot and slices it off the top edge towards third man. Matt Henry runs to his right and dives to take a fantastic catch just inches above the ground. Pakistan are 8/1!
On a length and on leg, Saud Shakeel flicks it away wide of deep square leg for a brace.
Back of a length and on off, Saud Shakeel dabs it to point.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam drills it wide of mid off. Mitchell Santner moves quickly to his right and dives to stop it well. A single is taken.
Hard length and on middle, Saud Shakeel pats it down to mid on.
Short of a length and on off, Saud Shakeel punches it to covers.
BEATEN! Matt Henry hits the length hard and just around off, takes off sharply, Saud Shakeel looks to guide it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length and on off, Saud Shakeel steers it wide of point. Glenn Phillips dives to his left to make a fin one-handed stop.
Full again and around off, Saud Shakeel drills it and finds the gap through covers for a couple of runs.
Fuller and on off, Saud Shakeel drives it firmly but straight to covers.
Hard length and on middle, shapes away, Saud Shakeel guides it to third man for a single.
Pulls his length back and on middle, Saud Shakeel looks to play at it but gets an inside edge towards square leg. Five dots in a row now!
Fuller one and on middle, Saud Shakeel knocks it to the right of short mid-wicket.
Back of a length and around off, shapes away, Saud Shakeel lets it go.
Close! Pitched up and on off, Saud Shakeel looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto his pads as the ball rolls just past the stumps.
Good length and in that channel outside off, angling away, Saud Shakeel leaves it alone.
Will O’Rourke begins with a fuller one but way outside off, shaping further away, Saud Shakeel fails to reach it. Wided.
Fullish and on middle, keeps low, Babar Azam does well to keep it out.
Overpitched and on middle, Babar Azam drills it to mid on.
Pakistan gets underway in the chase! On a length and on middle, Saud Shakeel nudges it towards mid-wicket or a single.
Goes full again and on off, Saud Shakeel drives it towards mid off.
Back of a length and on middle, Saud Shakeel looks to work it away but gets a leading edge safely towards point.
Matt Henry starts with a full delivery, on off, Saud Shakeel guides it off the outer half of the bat towards point.

A triple to end the innings then! Haris Rauf bangs this one short and on leg, Tom Latham pulls it towards deep square leg. The fielder from deep mid-wicket tries to pick it up but lets it through. However, deep square leg is aware and stops the ball from going to the boundary. Three runs taken. New Zealand finishes on 320/5!
Hard length and on leg, Michael Bracewell tries to heave it away but misses as the ball goes off his pads towards point. The batters crosses for a leg bye.

OUT! TAKEN! Finally another wicket for Pakistan! Haris Rauf takes pace off, full and on middle. Glenn Phillips looks for the reverse scoop but toe-ends it. The ball loops in the air towards short third where Fakhar Zaman takes a dolly. Phillips walks back for a smashing 61 off 39, and New Zealand are 316/5!

Another low full toss, angling in, Glenn Phillips jams it out off the toe-end of the bat towards long on and turns around for the second. Salman Agha throws it at the bowler's end where Haris Rauf fails to collect it and Latham makes his ground.

Haris Rauf loses his line and bowls this full but way down the leg side. Glenn Phillips leaves it alone and Mohammad Rizwan dives to his left but only to parry it behind. A wide is given and two byes taken as well.
FOUR! Powered away! A low full toss, on middle. Glenn Phillips backs away a bit and absolutely thrashes it wide of long off for a boundary.
Slower one, full and angling down the leg as he follows the batter. Tom Latham tries to slog but misses and gets hit on the pads as the ball rolls away. A leg bye is taken.
A good yorker to end the over, on leg, Tom Latham digs it out towards covers for one. 12 runs off the over!
A low full toss, outside off, Glenn Phillips reaches out for it and drills it to sweeper covers for one.
FOUR! Freebie! A loopy full toss, on middle. Glenn Phillips waits for it and thumps it over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Another yorker on middle, slower this time, angling in too. Glenn Phillips jams it out to point for one.

FOUR! That is a terrific shot! Nothing wrong with the delivery, but just class from the batter. Shaheen Afridi nails the yorker, on middle, shaping in. Tom Latham backs away and opens the face of his bat to squeeze it past point for a boundary.
FIFTY FOR PHILLIPS! He just loves playing against Pakistan and continues his good form here. Full and on middle, Glenn Phillips drills it to long on for a single.
A full toss, on off, Tom Latham drills it straight to point. That was there to be put away.
Pitched up and on off, slower too, Tom Latham goes down across to scoop but gets a toe-end towards deep mid-wicket for a brace. A better throw was needed there.
Fuller and on middle, Glenn Phillips drills it down the ground for a run.

An off-cutter, on a length and on middle, Tom Latham looks to slog it away but gets a top edge right onto his helmet. The ball goes towards the point as the batters take one. Latham looks a bit out of place but should be fine.

SIX! Just over! Haris Rauf goes slower, full and on middle, Tom Latham picks it up and swipes it towards deep square leg. Khushdil Shah is standing a few yards inside the ropes and tries to grab it with one hand but the ball sails over him for a six. If he was standing at the ropes, it would have been an easy catch.
Right in the blockhole, on middle, Glenn Phillips jams it out through mid-wicket for a single.
Overpitched and outside off, Glenn Phillips lofts it towards sweeper covers for one. 18 runs off the over!
SIX MORE! Glenn Phillips is playing a blinder here! Fuller one and on middle, angling in a bit. Phillips just picks it up and whips it over the deep square leg fence for another biggie.
SIX! SMASHED! Shaheen Afridi bangs this one short and on middle. Glenn Phillips gets on top of the bounce and hammers it to the deep mid-wicket fence for flat six.

HUNDRED FOR LATHAM! A fantastic knock for the Kiwi and he has been a rock for his team. Pitched up and on middle, Tom Latham works it towards long on for a single. He takes off his helmet and raises his bat to soak in all the applause.
Full again and on middle, Tom Latham drives it straight to short covers.
EDGED AND FOUR! Fuller one and on middle. Tom Latham looks to whip it over mid-wicket but gets a leading edge that flies over short third for a boundary. He moves to 99 now!
A low full toss, on middle, Tom Latham clips it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Short of a length and on middle, Glenn Phillips heaves it to deep square leg for one.
Bangs this into the pitch, on off, takes pace off, Tom Latham pulls it through mid-wicket for another run.
FOUR! Cheeky and effective! Fuller one and on middle. Tom Latham goes down across and scoops it over short fine for a boundary. He moves into the 90s now.
Slower bouncer around off, Glenn Phillips swats it through mid-wicket for a run.
Slower one, on a length and on middle, Tom Latham flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length and on middle, Glenn Phillips tucks it with soft hands through mid-wicket and comes back for the second run. 32 runs in the last 2 overs!

SIX! Oh..wow! Haris Rauf misses the yorker and serves this in the slot, on middle. Glenn Phillips once again with a straight bat launches it over the bowler's head for half a dozen more. 250 UP FOR NEW ZEALAND!
Fullish and around off, Tom Latham backs away and pushes it towards mid off for one.
Pitched up on middle, shaping in, Glenn Phillips drills it to long on for a single.
Full again and on middle, Glenn Phillips clips it wide of deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
FOUR! The floodgates are open now! Fuller one and angling on the pads. Glenn Phillips flicks it away easily past mid on for a boundary.

FOUR! Streay but the all count! Abrar Ahmed fires in a yorker, on off. Tom Latham goes down the sweep again but gets an inside edge that races to the fine leg fence for a boundary. 16 runs off the over!
Flatter, full and on middle, Tom Latham reverse sweeps it to short third.

FOUR! Put away! Tossed up, full and on the pads again. Tom Latham goes down again and swipes it away nicely to the deep square leg fence for a boundary now. Mohammad Rizwan is not happy with his bowler.
SIX! BOOM! The lefty goes big now! Flighted, full and down the leg. Tom Latham goes down on one knee and just helps it on its way over the fine leg fence for a bigie.
Short and around off, Glenn Phillips punches it to long off for a run.
Floated, full and on middle, Tom Latham sweeps it a bit uppishly but safely towards deep square leg for a single.
Pushed through quicker, short and angling into leg, Glenn Phillips misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
SIX! BANG! There he goes! Looped up, full and on middle. Glenn Phillips backs away a bit and tonks it over the bowler's head for a biggie.
Fires one full and on middle, angling in, Glenn Phillips knocks it to the right of the bowler.
Flighted, full and on leg, Glenn Phillips slogs it away wide of deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Glenn Phillips drills it on the bounce to the bowler.
Floated, full and on leg, Tom Latham comes down the track and tucks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Quicker, full and on middle, turns away, Glenn Phillips knocks it back to the bowler. Just 3 runs off the over. Excellent stuff!
Tossed up, full and on leg, Tom Latham goes down and reverse sweeps it through point for one.
Short and wide outside off, Glenn Phillips cuts it to deep point for a run.
Flighted, full and around off, Glenn Phillips drives it to short covers.
Flatter, short and on off, turns away, Glenn Phillips looks to punch but bunts it into the pitch.
Floated, full and down the leg, Tom Latham paddles it to short fine for a single.
Flighted, full and on off, Tom Latham uses his feet and cips it to deep mid-wicket for one more.
Continues to bowl short, on leg, Glenn Phillips nudges it through mid-wicket for one.
Another short delivery around off, Glenn Phillips punches it to covers.
Drags his length back, on middle, angling in, Glenn Phillips flicks it towards deep square leg and races back for the second run. Excellent running!
Quicker, shortish and outside off, skids through, Glenn Phillips tries to cut but misses.
Floated, short and on off, Tom Latham tucks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Good length around middle, Phillips clips it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length and outside off, Phillips makes room, opens the bat face, and punches it towards deep point for a couple of runs.
On the pads from a good length. Tom Latham flicks the ball to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Hits the length just outside off. Tom Latham drives the ball uppish to mid off.

SIX! FLICK OF A WRIST! Naseem Shah pitches the ball up on the legs of Tom Latham with pace. Tom Latham takes the front foot and flicks the ball up and over deep square leg for a massive six just by the use of his wrists.
BEATEN! Pitches the ball up outside the off stump line. Tom Latham looks to drive the ball but misses.
From around the wicket. Keeps it fuller and around the off stump. Phillips comes forward and drives it to short extra cover.
Good length and outside off, Tom Latham pushes it to sweeper cover for a single.
WIDE! Short of a length, well over the head of Latham. Latham ducks under it.
Good length outside off, Tom Latham pushes it away from the body and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Afridi goes fuller this time, around middle, Latham flicks it towards short mid wicket.
Back of a length around the leg stump. Phillips clips it to square leg for a single.
WIDE! Wayward outside the leg stump line. Wide called!
From over the wicket. On a good length on the fourth stump line. Latham comes forward and guides it to deep third man for a single.
Short and wide. Tom Latham tucks it away to sweeper covers for a run.
Nagging length at the batter. Glenn Phillips flicks the ball to deep square leg for a single to get off the mark.
Touch fuller on off. Glenn Phillips taps it to covers.
Hits the good length on top of the off stump. Glenn Phillips blocks it off the front foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! PAKISTAN BREAK THE PARTNERSHIP! Will Young's big knock comes to an end! Naseem Shah gets his man in the end but not before a marathon innings from the right-handed opener! Length ball on the off stump. angling back into the batter. Will Young goes for a wild slog and times it well but high in the air. The substitute fielder Faheem Ashraf runs in from deep mid-wicket to his right and grabs the catch with both hands. Will Young walks back for a well-made 107 (113) and New Zealand are now 191/4.
FOUR! SLAPPED! Over the wicket. Back of a length just outside the off stump. Young backs away and thrashes it between extra cover and deep cover for a cracking boundary.
Pitches the ball up on the off stump line. Tom Latham looks to play the on drive but gets a leading edge that falls short of covers.
Pitches the ball up outside the off stump. Tom Latham taps the ball to covers off the front foot.
Drops the ball short at the batter with pace. Tom Latham looks to pull the ball but misses.
Nagging length on top of the stumps. Tom Latham blocks it off the front foot.
Drops the length back outside off, and rolls his fingers across the ball. Tom Latham is beaten by pace and the ball goes back to Mohammad Rizwan on the bounce.

FOUR! SHOT! Glorious from Tom Latham! Shaheen Afridi pitches the ball up on the off stump from over the wicket angle. Tom Latham takes the front foot out and drives the ball into the covers gap to pick up a boundary all along the carpet. What a shot!
On a hard length on the body, Latham turns it around the corner in the short fine leg region for one.
Nagging length on top of the stumps. Will Young flicks the ball to deep square leg for a single.

Hits the length on top of the leg stump line. Tom Latham chips the ball up over mid on, off the front foot. Babar Azam puts in a good chase and stops the ball from going away to the boundary. Tom Latham picks up three runs and gets to a well-deserved FIFTY. Raises his bat to his team with joy.
WIDE! Wayward outside the leg stump line this time. Wide called by the umpire.
Tom Latham on 49, picks up the good length early and taps it down towards covers off the front foot.
Drops the length back outside off. Will Young drops the ball down to the left of point and runs a single.
LEG BYE! Nagging length on top of the leg stump. Tom Latham wears it on the thigh pads and runs a single from square leg.
A googly outside off, Latham pushes it through point to pick up a single and retain the strike for the next over.
On a nagging length outside off, Young punches it to sweeper in the off side for a single.
Tossed up full down leg, Young sweeps it but finds short fine leg.
Shorter in length on the stumps, Latham hangs back and flicks it past mid-wicket for a single. The 100-run partnership comes up between Tom Latham and Will Young!

Tossed up fuller on the off stump. Will Young gets down on a knee and sweeps the ball to deep square leg for a single. raises his bat to the crowd and his team as he becomes the person to score the first Hundred in the ICC Champions Trophy 2025. 4th batter from New Zealand to score a HUNDRED in the Champions Trophy history.
Just short outside off. Will Young taps it straight to the point. Still on 99!
Swings the ball into the left-hander from a good length on the stumps. Tom Latham flicks the ball to the right of fine leg and runs a quick couple to end the over.
FOUR! PULLED AWAY! Another bouncer from Haris Rauf at the batter with pace and Tom Latham pulls the ball well, probably waiting for it, and gets a boundary from fine leg.
Nagging length on top of off. Tom Latham drops it down from the crease.
Short stuff again from Haris Rauf and Tom Latham manages to block it off from the crease.
DROPPED! Another good bumper at the batter and Tom Latham pulls it uppish, towards mid-wicket. The fielder Salman Agha jumps up and manages to get a good hand to it, but does not hang on to the ball.

WIDE! DRAMA! Another good bumper across the batter from around the wicket angle. Tom Latham looks to pull the ball but the ball goes past very close to the gloves. The ball goes back to Mohammad Rizwan and he goes up for a caught behind appeal. The umpire says not out and signals wide. Mohammad Rizwan takes a review. The UltraEdge shows no glove involved and Pakistan lose a review.
A sharp bouncer by Rauf comes into the body, and Latham ducks under it.
Much fuller on the off stump. Will Young drives it well but straight back to the bowler. Stays on 99! End of the over.
Floats the ball up slow on the stumps. Will Young blocks it off the front foot.
Nagging length on off. Will Young punches it well but straight to covers.
Short and wide, cut away to sweeper covers for one.

Pitches the ball up on the stumps. Will Young looks to play a sweep shot but the ball hits his glove, goes over the keeper Mohammad Rizwan and runs down the fine leg fence. Haris Rauf puts in a good chase to stop the boundary but the batters run three. Moves onto 99 with that, Will Young.
Fuller on the off stump. Tom Latham drives it to long on for a single.

FOUR! INNOVATION AT IT'S BEST! Haris Rauf pitches the ball outside off, on a good length. Will Young plays it very late and the ball catches the bottom edge of the bat. The ball runs away to the third man fence beating the flying Mohammad Rizwan. Will Young moves onto 96 with that.
Hits the good length hard outside off. Tom Latham taps it to sweeper covers for a run.
Drops the ball short from around the wicket. Tom Latham picks it up early and pulls the ball infront of deep square leg for a quick couple.
Nagging length on the off stump. Tom Latham blocks it off the front foot.
Bowls on a good length once again. Will Young nudges it to third man and runs a single.
Hits the length hard on top of the off stump line. Will Young blocks it off the front foot.
Touch fuller on off. Will Young drives the ball to long off for one to end the over. Moves onto 91 with that single.
Tosses the ball up outside the off stump and gets a good turn into the batter. Will Young goes for a sweep and wears the ball high on the body. Appeal for LBW but the umpire says no.
Touch fuller on off. Will Young drives it back to the bowler.
Touch fuller on the off stump line. Tom Latham plays the paddle sweep to deep square leg for one.
Floats the ball up on off. Tom Latham taps it down to mid-wicket.
Tosses the ball up on off. Will Young sweeps it to deep square leg for one.
FOUR! And again! Tossed up, full and on middle. Tom Latham goes down on one knee and nails another sweep past square leg for four more runs.
Slows it up, short and on off, Tom Latham stabs it out on the pitch.
Floated, full and on off, Tom Latham knocks it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Nicely played! Flighted, full and on middle. Tom Latham goes down and rolls his arms nicely to play the sweep to the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Short again and on middle, Tom Latham pats it to short mid-wicket.
Short and around off, Will Young punches it through covers for a single.
Fuller again and on leg, Tom Latham tucks it nicely through mid-wicket for a brace.

An appeal for run out, and it has been sent upstairs! Overpitched and on middle, Will Young drills it towards mid on and sets off for the run. The fielder hits the stumps at the bowler's end but the replay shows that Young is safe.
Pitched up and on middle, Tom Latham knocks it wide of mid off for another run.
Good length and on off, Will Young pats it wide of backward point for a quick run.
FOUR! Up and over! Naseem Shah serves this a bit too full, on off. Will Young presents the full face of the bat and lofts it over mid off for a lovely boundary.
Short of a length and on middle, Tom Latham pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Flatter, full and on middle, Tom Latham works it to deep mid-wicket for one more.
Shorter in length again, on leg, Tom Latham flicks it to square leg.
Quicker, short and around off, Will Young slaps it through covers for one.
Flighted, full and on middle, Tom Latham clips it through mid-wicket for another run.
Short and outside off Will Young punches it to sweeper covers for a run.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Tom Latham knocks it to the left of the bowler. Khushdil Shah dives to that side but parries it away allowing a single.

FOUR! Excellent shot! Naseem Shah goes fuller and on middle, angling into the pads. Will Young clips it away with sublime timing. The outfield does the rest as the ball races to the deep square leg fence for a boundary. That also brings up the 50-run partnership between these two batters.
Good length and on middle, sticks to the surface a bit. Will Young looks to flick but gets a leading edge along the ground towards the bowler.
Touch fuller and on middle, Tom Latham guides it to third man for a single.
Hard length and on the fifth stump line, Tom Latham has no room to work with and pats it to point. Good bowling from Naseem Shah!
Back of a length and on off, Tom Latham dabs it to point.
Fuller and on off, angling away, Tom Latham taps it to short covers.
Quicker, full and on leg, Tom Latham works it to long on for one.
Flatter, full and on middle, Tom Latham steers it to point.
Flighted, full and on off, Tom Latham drives it past covers and comes back for the second run quite comfortably.
Floated, full and on middle, Will Young eases it to long on for another run.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Tom Latham sweeps it to deep square leg for a run.
Short and around off, Will Young move back and swats it on the bounce to wide long on for a single.
Back of a length and on off, Will Young dabs it through point for one.
Good length and on middle, Will Young stays back and blocks it out.
Short of a length and on off, Tom Latham pulls it to deep square leg for a run.
Fuller and on off, shaping in, Tom Latham knocks it to mid on.
Length again and around off, Will Young guides it to third man for a single. Nelson on the board.
On a length and on middle, Will Young pats it to short mid-wicket.
Looped up, full and on middle, Tom Latham keeps it out to the off side.
Flatter, full and on middle, Tom Latham knocks it back to the bowler.
Slows it up, full and on off, Tom Latham pushes it to short covers.
FOUR! Good shot! Flighted, full and on middle, angling in. Tom Latham goes down and executes the sweep to perfection to the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Floated, full and on off, Will Young reverse sweeps it without much timing towards short third for a run.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Will Young tucks it to short mid-wicket.
Overpitched and on middle, Will Young flicks it to deep square leg for one.
Pitched up and on off, Will Young drives it to short covers.
FOUR! Nice shot! Shaheen Afridi serves this full again and on middle, shaping in. Will Young brings his wrists into play and flicks it beautifully through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tries the yorker, on middle, swings in a bit too much, Tom Latham clips it through mid-wicket for a run. 100 UP FOR THE KIWIS!
Back of a length and on off, Will Young dabs it past point for a single.
On a length and on middle, angling in and keeps a bit low, Will Young adjusts well to block it out.
Goes short and around off, Will Young moves back and punches it through covers for one.
Flighted, full and on middle, Tom Latham eases it to long off for another run.
Quicker, full and on off, Tom Latham drills it to short covers.
Floated, full and on off, Will Young taps it towards backward point for a run.
Flatter, full and on off, Tom Latham drives it to long off for a single.
Tossed up, full and on off, Tom Latham steers it to point.
Touch fuller and on middle, angling in, Will Young tucks it to short mid-wicket.
Hard length and on off, nips back in a bit, Will Young looks to run it down to third man but chops it on to the off side.
Good length and on middle, Will Young fends it with a straight bat back to the bowler.
Back of a length and outside off, Tom Latham guides it to point for a single.
Full again and around off, Tom Latham pushes it straight to short covers.
Fuller and on off, shaping in, Tom Latham blocks it down the pitch.
Fuller again, around middle, Latham lunges and flicks it to long on for a single.
Floated up, around off, Latham comes forward and blocks it out back to the bowler.
Drags his length, around off, Young cuts it wide of cover for a single.
FOUR! INNOVATIVE AND CHEEKY! Khushdil Shah gives air to the ball and keeps it fuller, around off, Will Young lunges and sweeps it towards deep fine leg for a boundary.
Tossed up, around middle, Latham flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
A bit slower and follows the batter, around leg, Tom Latham shimmies down the track and looks to flick it but misses and wears it on the front pad.
Goes fuller this time, and outside off, Will Young strides forward and drives it wide of cover for a couple of runs.
Good comeback by Haris Rauf! Hard length, and outside off, gets the ball to move away, Will Young looks to cut it but gets beaten on the outside edge.

FOUR! PUNISHED! Haris is bowling on the same length again and again, back of a length, around off, Will Young is quick enough to go on the back foot and pulls it hard along the ground towards deep square leg for a boundary. There is no chance for the fielder in deep to even touch that ball. SHEER POWER!
On a good length, around middle, Young covers the line and drops it down back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Short of a length, well outside off, Will Young opens the face of the bat and looks to guide it towards deep third but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length, on the fourth stump, Young presses forward and dabs it towards point.
Nagging length, around middle, Young stays on the back foot and pushes it towards square leg for a single.
A bit quicker and around the pads, Will Young goes on the back foot and looks to flick it but gets it through the inner half of the bat towards square leg.
Nagging length, around off, Young steers it to extra cover off the front foot.
Floated up, around off, Latham comes forward and pushes it to long on for a single.
Tossed up, around middle, Latham defends it.

COULD HAVE BEEN CHOPPED ON! Khushdil drops it short, slower through the air, around middle, Will Young clears out his front leg and looks to play it to the off side but gets a thick inside edge as the ball zips past the leg stump. They run for a single as the ball rolls away towards short fine leg.

GETS HIS FIFTY WITH THIS SINGLE DOES WILL YOUNG! Back of a length, around middle, Young clips it wide of square leg for a single to complete his milestone! He gets a chance to play as Rachin Ravindra got injured and he has proved his worth as he has held up one end quite nicely and will want to make it big.
A tight single! On a good length, on the fourth stump, Latham taps it wide of cover point and runs off for a quick single.
Goes fuller but on the pads, easy for Tom Latham as he transfers his weight to the front foot and uses his wrists to flick it wide of square leg for a couple of runs to get off the mark.
Back of a length, just outside off, Tom Latham hops up and gets on the top of the bounce to drop it down towards point.

OUT! CAUGHT! HARIS RAUF BREAKS THE GROWING PARTNERSHIP! Daryl Mitchell will be livid with himself for playing this shot! He goes back for 10 (24). Haris comes in from over the wicket and bowls on the back of a length, around middle, Daryl Mitchell presses back and looks to pull it down the ground. He wants to play that tennis ball kind of shot but the ball gets big on him. He only manages to get it hit straight to the mid on fielder where Shaheen Afridi makes no mistake as he comes forward and takes it with reverse cup at low height. Pakistan are 73/3.
Back of a length, on the fourth stump, Daryl Mitchell moves across and hops up a bit to drop it down towards mid-wicket.
Fuller again, around middle, Young lunges and blocks it out back to the bowler. Just 2 off it.
Floated up, around off, Mitchell drives it to deep cover for a single.

BEATEN! Tossed up, slower through the air this time, turns away, Daryl Mitchell comes forward to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge big time. Mohammad Rizwan collects the ball and dislodges the bails but Mitchell is well inside of the crease.
On a nagging length, just outside off, turns away after pitching, Daryl Mitchell looks to drive it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Keeps it shorter again, around off, Young steers it to deep cover for a single.
Drops it short, outside off, Young rocks back and cuts it hard but straight to the backward point fielder.
On a good length, around off and middle, angling in, Will Young nudges it to deep square leg for a single.
Haris serves it full, around off, Young flicks it to mid on and wants to have a quick single but is sent back by Daryl Mitchell.
Hard length, around middle, seaming in, Daryl Mitchell lets the ball come to him and then tickles it towards deep fine leg for an easy single.
Goes fuller and on the pads, too easy for Young as he lunges and flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
On a good length, just outside off, Young dabs it to backward point.
JAFFA! Hard length, in the channel, a hint of outswing, Will Young opens the face of the bat off late and looks to guide it towards point but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Goes fuller, around middle, Young extends his arms and drives it to long off for a single.
Nagging length, around middle, Young clips it to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Floated up, turns away, around off, Will Young comes forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. Mohammad Rizwan also dislodges the bails behind the stumps but no harm done!
Keeps it shorter and outside off this time, Mitchell stays back and steers it to deep cover for a single.
Drags his length, around middle, Young goes back and turns it wide of mid-wicket for a single to rotate the strike.
Tossed up, around off, Mitchell reaches out with a long stride and drives it to long off for a single.
Nagging length, around off, Young defends it to cover.
On a good length, around leg, follows the batter, Daryl Mitchell makes room and chips it towards mid on for a quick single.
On a good length, around off, Mitchell comes forward and shows the full face of the bat to defend it back to the bowler.
WIDE! Sprays down the leg side, slightly fuller, and seaming in, Daryl Mitchell looks to flick it but misses. Called a wide.
Back of a length, around middle, Mitchell presses back and drops it down to mid-wicket.
On a good length, around middle, Young nudges it wide of mid-wicket for a single.

SIX! GREETS WITH THE FIRST MAXIMUM OF THE MATCH AND CHAMPIONS TROPHY! Haris bangs in short of a length, around middle, at a comfortable height, Will Young transfers his weight to the back foot and looks to pull it but it takes the top edge and goes over the ropes at deep backward square leg for a biggie.
Floated up, around off, Young comes forward and looks to defend it but gets it through the inner half of the bat towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! OFF THE EDGE! A bit quicker ball, around middle and leg, Will Young rocks back and looks to flick it but gets an inside edge as the ball races away to the boundary at deep fine leg.
Drops it short, around off, Will Young goes on the back foot and blocks it out.
A shout of catch from Rizwan! Tossed up, around off and middle, Will Young comes forward and flicks it aerially to the right of the bowler but is drops just ahead of the bowler.
Drags his length, and changes the line to the off stump, Will Young comes forward and defends it.
Arm ball, around middle, a bit quick, Young keeps it down towards mid-wicket off the front foot.
On a good length, around middle, Daryl Mitchell hops up and tucks it off his hips towards square leg for a couple of runs.
Hard length, around middle, coming in with the angle, Daryl Mitchell sits under it as the ball goes over him. Mitchell was asking for the wide from the umpire but it was going over the leg stump.
Naseen is bowling beautifully here in the channel! Back of a length, outside off, gets the ball to nip in, Daryl Mitchell ducks under it.

With a short leg, Naseem bangs in short of a length, around middle, comes in with the angle, Daryl Mitchell goes for the pull shot but the ball gets big on him and he gets cramped up for room. The ball goes past the outside edge of the bat to the keeper. There is an appeal for caught behind by Naseem and Rizwan asks him to take a review but they aren't going upstairs in the end.
Back of a length, outside off, stays a touch low, Daryl Mitchell shoulders his arms.
On a good length, outside off, Daryl Mitchell is standing well ahead of the crease as he moves across further and defends it to the pitch.
Much fuller on the off stump line. Will Young blocks it off the front foot.
Pitches the ball up on the leg stumps. Daryl Mitchell flicks it to the left of Shaheen Afridi at square leg and runs a single.
Nagging length on top of the stumps. Daryl Mitchell stays on the front foot and taps it down.
Tossed up on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it off the front foot.
Nagging length on the off stump. Will Young drives the ball to the right of covers and runs a single.
Fuller on the off stump. Daryl Mitchell drives the ball to long off for one.

FOUR! A GIFT! Naseem Shah bowls a half volley on the leg stump with pace. Will Young stays on the crease and flicks the ball up and over square leg for a superb boundary to end the over. Not a good finish for Naseem Shah after bowling a superb over.
BEATEN! Lovely delivery from a good length outside off. Will Young looks to poke at it form the crease and the ball zips past the outside edge of the bat.
Another short ball on top of the off stump. Daryl Mitchell walks in and flicks the ball to deep square leg for one.
A good bumper at the batter with pace. Daryl Mitchell stays back and drops the ball down on the crease.
Pitches the ball up on the off stump line. Daryl Mitchell walks in and taps it back to the bowler. Naseem Shah gives the batter a wild stare at the follow-through.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! MASSIVE BLOW FOR NEW ZEALAND! Kane Williamson walks back into the hut for just 1 (2). Naseem Shah gets the big fish! Pakistan are running away with control inside the powerplay! Beautiful length just outside the off stump and gets the ball to nip away. Kane Williamson looks to drop the ball on the crease but only manages a faint outside edge back to the wicketkeeper Mohammad Rizwan does not make a mistake. Naseem Shah runs away with the wicket and New Zealand are 40/2 now.
Much fuller on the off stump. Will Young blocks it off the front foot towards mid-wicket.
Nagging length outside off. Will Young slices it straight to point.
Much fuller on the off stump. Kane Williamson drives the ball to long off for a single to get off the mark straight away.

OUT! TIMBER! BIG WICKET FOR PAKISTAN! Abrar Ahmed gets rid of Devon Conway on 10 (17). Bowls a carrom ball on a nagging length on the middle stump line from over the wicket angle. The left-hander gets back in the crease and looks to block the ball. The ball nips away from the batter after pitching and zips past the outside edge of the bat. It goes on to hit the top of the off stump. Pakistan is up with joy! New Zealand are 39/1 now.
Nagging length on off. Devon Conway taps it down towards covers.
Pitches the ball up on the off stump line. Devon Conway blocks it off the front foot.
LEG BYE! Nagging length with a bit of movement into the batter on top of the stumps. Devon Conway wears it high on the thigh pads and the ball drops on the crease. The batters run a quick single.
Hits the good length on the off stump line. Devon Conway takes a foot out and drops the ball down.
Hits the length on the off stump. Will Young drops it towards point and runs a quicks single.

FOUR! PACE OFF! Naseem Shah takes pace off and pitches the ball up outside the off stump line. Will Young takes the front foot out and plays it up and over covers for a superb boundary. Timed to perfection!
Nagging length outside off. Will Young drops the ball towards point.
Pitches the ball up on the off stump. Will Young drives the ball back to the bowler.
Nagging length on the leg stump. Devon Conway blocks it off the front foot to end the over.
Pitches it up on off. Devon Conway offers a good front foot defence.
Much fuller on the off stump line. Will Young drives it to long off for one.
Nagging length on off. Will Young drops it down on the crease.
Fuller on off. Will Young drives it back to the bowler.
Much fuller on the off stump. Devon Conway drives the ball back and hits the stumps on the bowler's end. The batters run a single off the ricochet.
WIDE! Starts off wayward outside the leg stump. Wide called by the umpire.

FOUR! ENDS THE OVER WELL! Shot of the day so far from Will Young! Shaheen Afridi provides a little bit of width outside the off stump line and Will Young catches onto it well. Takes the front foot out and times the ball behind point for a beautiful boundary.
Just short on the stumps. Will Young flicks the ball to the left of mid-wicket and denies the single. Good work at mid-wicket.
Good length delivery angling across Young who presses forward and defends it to covers.
Drops the ball short on the stumps. Will Young flicks the ball to the right of mid-wicket and runs a quick couple.
Pitches it further up on the off stump. Will Young blocks it off the front foot.
Bowls on a good length on top of the off stump. Will Young stands tall on the crease and drops the ball down.
Hits the good length on off. Devon Conway watchfully taps it straight to point to end the over.
Pitches the ball up outside the off stump line. Will Young works it down to third man and runs a single.
Much fuller on the off stump. Will Young drives it back to Naseem Shah.
Hits the deck hard on top of the stumps. Will Young drops the ball back at the bowler.
Nagging length on the stumps. Will Young tucks it to the right of mid-wicket and runs a couple.

FOUR! EASY PICKINGS! Will Young gets a gift from Naseem Shah to pick up his first boundary of the innings. Naseem Shah strays down the leg side, fuller with just 3 fielders on the leg side. Will Young flicks the ball fine and gets a boundary to his name at deep fine leg.
Pitches the ball up on the off stump. Will Young taps the ball short of mid on and runs a quicks single to end the over. Excellent running between the wickets.
Short and wide outside off. Devon Conway tucks it to sweeper covers for one.

FOUR! IN THE GAP! Devon Conway gets his second boundary of the innings. Shaheen Afridi drops the length back at the batter from over the wicket angle. Devon Conway stands still and pulls the ball fine enough to get it in the fine leg gap for a boundary.

Pitches the ball up on the off stump and gets the ball to go straight with the arm. Will Young looks to flick the ball but adjusts it in the end, getting a thick leading edge that goes between covers and point. Another good chase to the boundary line that allows the batters to pick up three runs.
Holds the length back on off. Young stays back and taps it down.
Good length delivery on the off stump line. Will Young walks in and drops the ball towards mid on.
Drops the length back and gets the ball to move away from the left-hander. Devon Conway looks to play it but misses the ball.

FOUR! FIRST BOUNDARY OF THE CHAMPIONS TROPHY 2025! Naseem Shah pitches the ball up on the off stump and gets the ball to swing into the left-hander from over the wicket angle. Devon Conway looks to drive the ball off the front foot and gets the inside half of the bat that takes the ball into the gap between mid-wicket and square leg. The timing is still good enough to take the ball away to the fence.
Touch fuller on the off stump. Will Young walks in and flicks the ball towards mid on for a quick single.
Hits the good length outside off again. Will Young sees it through.

BEATEN! That is a superb delivery from Naseem Shah as he drops the length back just outside off and gets the ball to swing away. Will Young looks to feel for it but gets beaten on the outside edge. Smiles all around the bat.
Swings the ball away from the right-hander from outside off. Will Young sees it through to Mohammad Rizwan.
Drops the length back on top of the stumps. Devon Conway stays back and drops the ball down on the crease to end the first over of the innings. New Zealand are 3/0.
Pitches the ball up on the off stump line. Devon Conway blocks it off well towards covers.

Runs in hard from over the wicket and pitches the ball on a good length on off. The ball nips back into the left-hander. Devon Conway is caught on the crease and gets a hit high up on the thigh pads. Huge appeal from the Pakistan players but the umpire is unmoved.
Drops the ball short outside off to the left-hander. Devon Conway stays back and punches the ball well but straight to point.

Pitches this much fuller outside the off stump line from over the wicket angle. Will Young plays a beautiful cover drive in the gap and starts running. Fakhar Zaman makes a good run behind the ball and manages to pull it back. Might have hurt himself in the process. The batters run three runs.
Starts off over the wicket and hits the perfect length on top of the off stump. Will Young takes a good front foot out and taps it down. The Champions Trophy has begun!
